{"kind":"article","abstract":[{"text":"If you don’t know about RFID, this article will introduce you to some basic knowledge so that you can better understand the SDK..","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/com.rfid.RFIDManager\/documentation\/RFIDManager\/RFID-related-document"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"RFID-Tag-Data-Structure","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"RFID Tag Data Structure"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The plugin’s functionality is designed and developed around RFID tags. Understanding some basic information about RFID tags can help better comprehend the RFID-related features.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The basic data areas of an RFID tag are roughly as shown below:","type":"text"}]},{"text":"Data Regions Explanation:","anchor":"Data-Regions-Explanation","level":3,"type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"RESERVED"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Contains two password fields: kill and access, each 32 bits long. Default password is 00000000."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"EPC"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Contains three components:","type":"text"}]},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"crc: Cyclic Redundancy Check"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"pc: epc length control word"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"epc: Actual EPC user data"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"The length of the epc data read during inventory is determined by the upper 5 bits of the pc value.","type":"text"},{"text":"\n","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"Examples of epc length to pc value conversion:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n"},{"type":"text","text":"For an epc length of 6 words (96 bits)： 6 word = "},{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"0011 0"}]},{"type":"text","text":"000 0000 0000 = 0x3000"},{"text":"\n","type":"text"},{"text":"For an epc length of 9 words (144 bits)： 9 word = ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"0100 1"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":"000 0000 0000 = 0x4800"},{"text":"\n","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"For an epc length of 15 words (240 bits)： 15 word = "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"0111 1"}],"type":"strong"},{"text":"000 0000 0000 = 0x7800","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"TID"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Contains only tid data. Typically 96 bits, unique and unmodifiable.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"USER","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Contains only user data. Length varies by tag type.","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"orderedList"}]}],"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/com.rfid.RFIDManager\/documentation\/RFIDManager"]]},"seeAlsoSections":[{"anchor":"Developing-with-RFIDManager","title":"Developing with RFIDManager","identifiers":["doc:\/\/com.rfid.RFIDManager\/tutorials\/Meet-RFIDManager","doc:\/\/com.rfid.RFIDManager\/documentation\/RFIDManager\/RFIDManager-FAQ"],"generated":true}],"metadata":{"modules":[{"name":"RFIDManager"}],"roleHeading":"Article","role":"article","title":"RFID Document"},"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/rfidmanager\/rfid-related-document"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"references":{"doc://com.rfid.RFIDManager/documentation/RFIDManager":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.rfid.RFIDManager\/documentation\/RFIDManager","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/rfidmanager","abstract":[{"text":"A framework for UHF RFID tag reading, writing, and management on Apple platforms.","type":"text"}],"title":"RFIDManager","role":"collection"},"doc://com.rfid.RFIDManager/documentation/RFIDManager/RFIDManager-FAQ":{"type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.rfid.RFIDManager\/documentation\/RFIDManager\/RFIDManager-FAQ","kind":"article","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"This document mainly introduces some common problems you may encounter when using RFIDManager"}],"url":"\/documentation\/rfidmanager\/rfidmanager-faq","title":"RFIDManager-FAQ","role":"article"},"doc://com.rfid.RFIDManager/tutorials/Meet-RFIDManager":{"url":"\/tutorials\/meet-rfidmanager","type":"topic","identifier":"doc:\/\/com.rfid.RFIDManager\/tutorials\/Meet-RFIDManager","title":"Meet RFIDManager","kind":"overview","role":"overview","abstract":[{"type":"text","text":"This tutorial will guide you through importing the RFIDManager library into your project and show you how to use it."}]}}}